    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the Menominee, an indigenous people whose native land is in the present-day state of Wisconsin. The name "Menominee" derives from the Algonkian word for "manomin," a word for rice.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
